248
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,718
This boy needs to be hospitalized.

249
00:15:27,927 --> 00:15:29,469
I don't have health insurance.

250
00:15:29,679 --> 00:15:32,139
That's okay,
St. Peter's will take indigent cases.

251
00:15:32,348 --> 00:15:36,351
-Pack some things for the hospital tonight.
DIANNE: What, like clothes? What?

252
00:15:36,519 --> 00:15:39,605
[SIREN WAILING]

253
00:15:42,817 --> 00:15:45,819
You telling the truth, son?
About what you all saw.

254
00:15:46,029 --> 00:15:47,821
Don't you believe me?

255
00:15:48,031 --> 00:15:50,324
I didn't say I didn't believe you.

256
00:15:50,658 --> 00:15:52,451
Just seems strange, that's all.

257
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:55,912
You called 911,
but you wouldn't leave your name.

258
00:15:56,164 --> 00:15:58,790
Well, I was scared.
It was the first dead guy I ever saw.

259
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:02,085
Why'd you sneak back and hide
up in the woods where I found you?

260
00:16:02,295 --> 00:16:05,297
I don't know.
I just wanted to see, I guess.

261
00:16:05,465 --> 00:16:06,882
HARDY:
Hmm.

262
00:16:07,884 --> 00:16:11,261
Did you talk to the man
before he killed himself?

263
00:16:11,471 --> 00:16:13,597
No, I never talked to him.

264
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:16,224
Name "Jerome Clifford"
mean anything to you?

265
00:16:16,434 --> 00:16:18,101
No.

266
00:16:20,063 --> 00:16:23,649
You know, I found some
fresh cigarette butts near the body.

267
00:16:23,858 --> 00:16:26,151
Same brand as your mama smokes.

268
00:16:26,361 --> 00:16:30,739
Somehow I can't see you finding the body
and then deciding to have a cigarette.

269
00:16:30,907 --> 00:16:31,948
[SIGHS]

270
00:16:32,116 --> 00:16:35,535
Look, officer, all that happened was
we was just walking through the woods...

271
00:16:35,745 --> 00:16:37,579
...when we found Romey dead. That's all.

272
00:16:37,789 --> 00:16:40,040
-Who's Romey?
-That's the guy's name, isn't it?

273
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:42,876
I said, Jerome Clifford.

274
00:16:43,086 --> 00:16:44,753
Whoever heard of the name Romey?

275
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:02,437
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

276
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:06,400
GREENWAY:
I'm Dr. Greenway. Is this your son?

277
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:07,609
DIANNE:
Yeah, he's my son.

278
00:17:07,777 --> 00:17:09,569
GREENWAY: What's his name?
DIANNE: Ricky Sway.

279
00:17:09,737 --> 00:17:13,073
GREENWAY: How long has he been this way?
-I didn't find him, my other boy, Mark, did.

280
00:17:13,282 --> 00:17:16,326
You found him, Mark? Ricky?
Is that what you called him? Ricky?

281
00:17:16,494 --> 00:17:19,621
REPORTER 1 [ON TV]: Jerome R. Clifford,
New Orleans attorney, was found dead...

282
00:17:19,789 --> 00:17:23,083
...in an apparent suicide
outside Memphis just hours ago.

283
00:17:23,292 --> 00:17:26,795
The famed Mafia lawyer was due
to defend the alleged Mafia hit man...

284
00:17:27,004 --> 00:17:29,339
...Barry "The Blade" Muldano
next month...

285
00:17:29,549 --> 00:17:33,260
...in the increasingly notorious case
of still-missing Louisiana senator...

286
00:17:33,469 --> 00:17:36,388
...Boyd Boyette, now presumed dead.

287
00:17:36,556 --> 00:17:38,181
REPORTER 2:
It was going to be tough...

288
00:17:38,349 --> 00:17:40,350
...to build a case against Muldano
without a body...

289
00:17:40,518 --> 00:17:43,145
...but surely Clifford's death
will mean more delays.

290
00:17:43,354 --> 00:17:45,397
As one informed source tells me...

291
00:17:45,606 --> 00:17:48,692
...the plot thickens and sickens
for U.S. Attorney Roy Foltrigg.

292
00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:51,611
REPORTER 3:
No body, no case, no conviction.

293
00:17:51,821 --> 00:17:55,282
And that means no front-page pictures
that Attorney Foltrigg likes so much.

294
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:59,327
REPORTER 3: No CNN interviews,
no speedy ascent to Capitol Hill.

295
00:17:59,537 --> 00:18:01,455
Sorry, Reverend Roy.

296
00:18:01,664 --> 00:18:05,375
-I never liked that old cow.
DRIVER: We're here, Roy.

297
00:18:08,963 --> 00:18:12,966
He tried it first with a garden hose
attached to the tailpipe, but it didn't work.

298
00:18:13,176 --> 00:18:14,426
He was probably too stoned.

299
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:17,053
He was full of downers
and about a gallon of whiskey.

300
00:18:17,263 --> 00:18:20,932
Guess he figured he'd swallow a bullet
for dessert. Single gunshot to the head.

301
00:18:21,142 --> 00:18:23,435
-Cheap snub-nosed .38.
-A definite suicide, Roy.

302
00:18:23,644 --> 00:18:25,771
Damn him.
I called Romey two days ago, I said:

303
00:18:25,980 --> 00:18:28,815
"I have enough evidence
to pierce client-attorney privilege. ..

304
00:18:29,025 --> 00:18:32,527
...and put your fat ass on the stand."
I was bullshitting him, of course.

305
00:18:32,737 --> 00:18:35,030
I was trying to get him nervous,
see if he'd talk.

306
00:18:35,239 --> 00:18:38,200
Didn't know he'd blow his scalp off.
He must've known where that body's at.

307
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:41,870
MAN 1: Oh, he's never gonna tell us now.
Without that body we got no case.

308
00:18:42,079 --> 00:18:45,165
ROY: How's the weather in Memphis?
MAN 3: It's hot, Roy.

309
00:18:47,543 --> 00:18:48,585
Sprite?

310
00:18:55,092 --> 00:18:58,804
-What happened to your face?
-I got in a fight at school.

311
00:18:59,013 --> 00:19:01,515
It's summer. There's no school.

312
00:19:01,724 --> 00:19:03,850
I meant, a kid from my school.

313
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:05,727
-Who was the kid?
-Why?

314
00:19:05,937 --> 00:19:10,524
Why? Because I'm a cop.
It's my job to ask questions.

315
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:13,693
Besides, I think your story's full of holes.

316
00:19:13,903 --> 00:19:16,530
I believe you were in that car
before Clifford died.

317
00:19:17,323 --> 00:19:18,865
What does "indigent" mean?

318
00:19:19,075 --> 00:19:20,742
Indigent?

319
00:19:21,369 --> 00:19:22,494
That means "poor."

320
00:19:22,912 --> 00:19:25,914
Like you and your mother
and your little brother.

321
00:19:26,123 --> 00:19:27,749
So you better tell the truth.. .

322
00:19:27,959 --> 00:19:30,126
...hope it snaps him out of it.

323
00:19:30,336 --> 00:19:31,461
Otherwise. ..

324
00:19:31,671 --> 00:19:37,008
...he could lie in some institution
for dirt-poor crazy people.. .

325
00:19:37,426 --> 00:19:41,304
...with padded walls and cockroaches.. .

326
00:19:41,514 --> 00:19:45,058
...and, uh, chained to some filthy bed
with snakes--

327
00:19:46,894 --> 00:19:47,936
Mark. ..

328
00:19:48,688 --> 00:19:51,189
... I'm Karen. Will you come with me?

329
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:59,531
MARK: Bye.
-Bye.

330
00:20:02,285 --> 00:20:04,870
-We're gonna have to watch him.
DIANNE: What are you gonna do?

331
00:20:05,079 --> 00:20:08,290
GREENWAY: We're just gonna watch for
now. Sometimes just a good night's sleep...

332
00:20:08,499 --> 00:20:11,001
...and they wake up,
they don't know what's going on.

333
00:20:11,210 --> 00:20:12,544
His reflexes seem to be good.

334
00:20:12,753 --> 00:20:14,212
-That's good.
-Yeah.

335
00:20:14,422 --> 00:20:17,340
Mark, honey, Ricky's real sick.

336
00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:20,927
-What's the matter with him?
-It's called post-traumatic stress syndrome.

337
00:20:21,137 --> 00:20:23,930
Sometimes a person sees something
they just can't deal with.

338
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:29,769
I'm always telling Mark,
"No horror movies. No scary comics."

339
00:20:29,979 --> 00:20:32,230
Not for Ricky.

340
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:35,984
-He's always been tender that way.
GREENWAY: Easy, now.

341
00:20:36,193 --> 00:20:38,695
DIANNE: You try to protect them,
there's just so bad out there.

342
00:20:38,905 --> 00:20:42,282
GREENWAY: Why don't you get some rest
yourself? Why don't you lie down and rest?

343
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:45,911
There's nothing more you can do.
We're just gonna watch him.

344
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:49,205
You've had a rough day.
Just lie down in here. Stay with him.

345
00:21:04,889 --> 00:21:06,806
BEALE:
Boy, that's a bad injury. What happened?

346
00:21:07,016 --> 00:21:10,018
MAN: Car wreck. Got hit by an oil truck.
Nut run a stop sign.

347
00:21:10,227 --> 00:21:13,772
BEALE: My name's Gill Beale, I'm a lawyer.
You got a problem, I can fix it.

348
00:21:13,981 --> 00:21:16,691
I specialize in car wrecks,
especially large trucks.

349
00:21:16,901 --> 00:21:21,529
Let's see what you got. A broken leg,
a concussion, a couple of busted ribs--

350
00:21:21,739 --> 00:21:23,657
-And a broken collarbone.
-Great.

351
00:21:23,866 --> 00:21:26,660
I can get you at least 600,000.
We'll file suit tomorrow.

352
00:21:28,913 --> 00:21:32,374
Did I say six? Six is just for starters.
Here, check me out.

353
00:21:32,583 --> 00:21:34,709
Call up Gill Beale,
you'll see who's for real.

354
00:21:34,919 --> 00:21:37,796
More lawyers around this place
than there are doctors.

355
00:21:38,005 --> 00:21:41,925
Now, don't be that way.
I'm gonna outrun that little buggy of yours.

356
00:22:01,112 --> 00:22:04,030
-Wait till you get a load of this guy.
-All right.

357
00:22:04,699 --> 00:22:06,825
Mr. Foltrigg, Jason McThune, FBI.

358
00:22:07,034 --> 00:22:10,245
Welcome to Memphis, home of the king.
City of the good abode.

359
00:22:10,454 --> 00:22:11,871
ROY:
What do you know, McThune?

360
00:22:12,081 --> 00:22:15,792
Uh, kid's name is Mark Sway. He told Memphis
P.D. that he and his younger brother...

361
00:22:16,002 --> 00:22:19,504
...just stumbled on the body in the woods,
and then ran and called the cops.

362
00:22:19,714 --> 00:22:21,214
-I think he's lying.
-Why's that?

363
00:22:21,424 --> 00:22:23,258
We lifted his prints off a Sprite can...

364
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:26,428
...they match prints that
were all over the car, inside and out.

365
00:22:26,637 --> 00:22:29,222
I think he was in that car
before Clifford shot himself.

366
00:22:29,432 --> 00:22:32,267
And he was there for a while
because of the number of prints.

367
00:22:32,476 --> 00:22:34,394
-Why would the kid lie?
-One, he's scared.

368
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:37,105
Two, he's a kid, they always lie.
Adults are the enemy.

369
00:22:37,314 --> 00:22:41,026
And three, maybe Romey Clifford told him
something he knows he should not know.

370
00:22:41,235 --> 00:22:43,570
People hate to die with secrets.
That's good work, McThune.

371
00:22:43,738 --> 00:22:47,240
Ha, thank you very much, sir.
I'm gonna keep it up, believe me.

372
00:22:47,450 --> 00:22:51,578
Listen, ah, I'm sick and tired of chasing
Elvis sightings.

373
00:22:51,746 --> 00:22:54,080
I wanna get out of here.
Is there any room on your staff?

374
00:22:54,290 --> 00:22:55,999
-Where you wanna go?
-Anywhere you go.

375
00:22:56,167 --> 00:22:57,959
Gotta do something
about that hair first, heh.

376
00:22:58,127 --> 00:22:59,169
Yes, sir, ha, ha.

377
00:22:59,336 --> 00:23:01,546
-Meantime, I wanna talk to that child.
-Right away, sir.

378
00:23:06,594 --> 00:23:09,679
Dr. Greenway wants to see you.

379
00:23:10,848 --> 00:23:12,140
MARK:
How old are you?

380
00:23:12,349 --> 00:23:14,476
Twenty-four. Why?

381
00:23:14,685 --> 00:23:16,352
Are you married?

382
00:23:16,562 --> 00:23:18,521
Sometimes.

383
00:23:21,067 --> 00:23:23,693
DIANNE: I don't know nothing,
but he looks better to me.

384
00:23:23,903 --> 00:23:27,405
I think if we get him home and get him
in his own bed, he's gonna be fine.

385
00:23:27,615 --> 00:23:29,324
I don't know why you just can't. ..

386
00:23:29,700 --> 00:23:32,077
-Mrs. Sway.
-...give him some medicine or something.

387
00:23:32,286 --> 00:23:35,705
Can't you just give him a shot
or something? I gotta go to work.

388
00:23:35,956 --> 00:23:39,084
-Our trailer park takes rent by the week.
-Listen to me.

389
00:23:39,293 --> 00:23:44,589
Right now, it's as if Ricky's in a dark place
and he's trying to find the way out.

390
00:23:44,799 --> 00:23:46,716
-Now, what's very important-- Listen to me.
-Ugh.

391
00:23:46,926 --> 00:23:49,636
What's very important
is that when he finds that way out...

392
00:23:49,845 --> 00:23:52,430
...the first thing he sees is your face.

393
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:55,850
Let's hope it'll only take a day or two.

394
00:23:56,060 --> 00:23:59,854
There goes another job. Must be
damn near setting some kind of record.

395
00:24:00,064 --> 00:24:02,690
I'll call your employer,
I'm sure he's gonna understand--

396
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:04,609
My employer runs a sweatshop, doctor.

397
00:24:04,819 --> 00:24:08,029
He will not send flowers.
He will not understand.

398
00:24:08,239 --> 00:24:09,906
You could take shifts.

399
00:24:10,116 --> 00:24:12,367
-Perhaps the father could come in--?
-Ex-father.

400
00:24:12,576 --> 00:24:14,536
And you keep him away from Ricky.

401
00:24:14,745 --> 00:24:17,122
-Now hush.
-Okay, Mom, I'm sorry.

402
00:24:17,289 --> 00:24:18,331
[GREENWAY CLEARS THROAT]

403
00:24:18,499 --> 00:24:21,251
Uh, I don't know if you've seen this...

404
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:25,588
...but there are policemen downstairs
and reporters.

405
00:24:25,798 --> 00:24:27,757
The FBI is coming
to interview Mark at 10.

406
00:24:27,967 --> 00:24:30,260
Mom, I don't wanna talk to them.

407
00:24:30,469 --> 00:24:33,179
I'm gonna wind up like Ricky
if they don't stop bugging me.

408
00:24:33,389 --> 00:24:37,308
-They're not gonna go away.
-I don't give a flying shit about the FBI.

409
00:24:37,518 --> 00:24:39,686
-You are getting on my last nerve.
-Mrs. Sway--

410
00:24:39,895 --> 00:24:42,897
Would you sit down and hush up?
I don't know what the hell to do.

411
00:24:43,107 --> 00:24:46,442
-Can I see you outside?
-I feel like I'm losing my mind.

412
00:24:46,652 --> 00:24:49,362
Telling me to wait for my boy to--
Some crap.

413
00:24:50,447 --> 00:24:51,865
[SWAY SIGHS]

414
00:24:52,908 --> 00:24:54,367
Mom?

415
00:24:54,577 --> 00:24:58,037
-This boy.
-I'm sorry.

416
00:25:00,124 --> 00:25:01,499
I'm sorry too.

417
00:25:01,709 --> 00:25:05,253
I'll think of something
to get us out of this, I promise.

418
00:25:05,462 --> 00:25:09,299
Hey. You and Ricky just found
that guy dead.

419
00:25:09,508 --> 00:25:11,176
Right?

420
00:25:11,969 --> 00:25:15,221
Come on now, there's nothing
you ain't telling me, is there?

421
00:25:16,348 --> 00:25:19,142
Dr. Greenway wants to start you on Valium,
Mrs. Sway.

422
00:25:19,810 --> 00:25:20,852
Those cost extra?

423
00:25:21,061 --> 00:25:23,479
KAREN: Yeah, don't worry about that,
just take these here.

424
00:25:23,689 --> 00:25:25,023
-Both of them?
-Both of them.

425
00:25:25,232 --> 00:25:26,816
You're gonna start feeling better.

426
00:25:27,026 --> 00:25:28,693
-Don't go far.
MARK: Okay, Mom.

427
00:25:30,321 --> 00:25:32,864
HARDY:
FBI, huh? Whoo!

428
00:25:33,324 --> 00:25:37,035
You know, I hear that they're sending
the Reverend Roy Foltrigg himself.

429
00:25:37,244 --> 00:25:39,245
That's bad. That's.. ..

430
00:25:39,455 --> 00:25:42,040
You know that the FBI...

431
00:25:42,249 --> 00:25:45,126
...puts kids in jail if they break the law?

432
00:25:46,003 --> 00:25:49,380
And if a kid has been involved
in a murder.. .

433
00:25:49,590 --> 00:25:53,092
...they got a special little, uh,
kid-sized electric chair.

434
00:25:53,302 --> 00:25:56,095
I saw it once. It was about...so high.

435
00:25:56,764 --> 00:26:01,059
Did you know that when somebody gets
electrocuted, the current is so strong. ..

436
00:26:01,268 --> 00:26:04,270
...it makes the blood in the veins boil.

437
00:26:04,438 --> 00:26:05,772
[MAKES CRACKLING SOUND]

438
00:26:05,940 --> 00:26:07,440
God.

439
00:26:07,650 --> 00:26:09,734
Fry you up just like a piece of bacon.

440
00:26:10,277 --> 00:26:13,488
-You're the only pig around here.
-Oh.

441
00:26:13,656 --> 00:26:15,114
See you later, Markus.

442
00:26:17,826 --> 00:26:20,954
[REPORTERS CHATTERING]

443
00:26:25,376 --> 00:26:27,210
REPORTER 1:
Are you here to question Mark Sway?

444
00:26:27,378 --> 00:26:29,379
I beg your pardon?

445
00:26:30,506 --> 00:26:31,965
REPORTER 2:
Are you here in Memphis. ..

446
00:26:32,132 --> 00:26:34,384
...to improve your own position
regarding the case, sir?

447
00:26:34,551 --> 00:26:38,304
My real interest is to see justice done.
Every one of you knows that about me.

448
00:26:38,472 --> 00:26:40,265
REPORTER 3:
Are you ever gonna find that body?

449
00:26:40,432 --> 00:26:43,226
ROY: We're gonna locate the senator's body.
You can count on that.

450
00:26:43,394 --> 00:26:45,561
REPORTER 4:
What do you think Mark Sway knows?

451
00:27:16,135 --> 00:27:18,845
You ain't gonna run here by yourself.

452
00:27:19,054 --> 00:27:21,597
-What do you want, boy?
-I need to see Mr. Beale.

453
00:27:21,807 --> 00:27:24,434
-Where are your parents?
-Where are yours?

454
00:27:24,643 --> 00:27:27,520
-Are you even injured?
-Do I look injured?

455
00:27:27,730 --> 00:27:29,772
Well, we only do injuries.

456
00:27:29,982 --> 00:27:33,568
Well, I'll just go get hit by a truck
and come back.

457
00:27:33,736 --> 00:27:35,528
[PHONE BUZZES]

458
00:27:35,696 --> 00:27:37,196
You all shut up too.

459
00:27:46,373 --> 00:27:49,751
-Yes?
-Hell, no.

460
00:27:53,505 --> 00:27:56,174
WOMAN: What the hell's wrong
with this damn window?

461
00:27:56,383 --> 00:27:57,425
Where you going?

462
00:27:57,634 --> 00:28:01,220
I'm gonna pick up something to eat
and then swing by the post office.

463
00:28:01,430 --> 00:28:03,264
WOMAN:
All right.

464
00:28:09,271 --> 00:28:11,939
Hey. When's your boss coming back?

465
00:28:12,107 --> 00:28:13,566
WOMAN:
Ugh, may I help you?

466
00:28:13,776 --> 00:28:16,027
No, I need to see Reggie Love.

467
00:28:16,195 --> 00:28:17,570
WOMAN:
Why, may I ask?

468
00:28:17,780 --> 00:28:19,864
Well, that's between me and Mr. Love.

469
00:28:20,824 --> 00:28:22,450
I'm Reggie Love.

470
00:28:22,618 --> 00:28:25,119
Pssh, a woman lawyer, oh, great.

471
00:28:25,329 --> 00:28:28,039
I think so. Now, why is it
you think you want a lawyer?

472
00:28:28,248 --> 00:28:31,125
I don't want a lawyer. I hate lawyers.

473
00:28:31,335 --> 00:28:34,295
Every lawyer I ever had
just shafted me and my mom.

474
00:28:34,505 --> 00:28:38,299
I said I need a lawyer.
But I don't know about no woman.

475
00:28:38,717 --> 00:28:41,928
Well, this lawyer that shafted you,
what was her name?

476
00:28:42,137 --> 00:28:43,971
It wasn't no her, it was a he.

477
00:28:44,932 --> 00:28:46,766
Right.

478
00:28:47,309 --> 00:28:50,395
Well, why is it that you think
you need a lawyer?

479
00:28:50,604 --> 00:28:53,064
-Because I'm Mark Sway.
-So?

480
00:28:53,565 --> 00:28:57,276
You know, the kid who found the dead guy.
I'm famous. Don't you read the paper?

481
00:28:57,486 --> 00:28:59,362
You still haven't answered my question.

482
00:28:59,571 --> 00:29:03,032
Because I'm supposed to talk to some
Reverend Roy guy in 10 minutes.

483
00:29:03,242 --> 00:29:06,244
-Reverend Roy Foltrigg?
-Yeah, why's everybody call him that?

484
00:29:06,453 --> 00:29:08,496
He loves to quote the scriptures
in court...

485
00:29:08,705 --> 00:29:10,873
...and knows the Bible
better than God himself.

486
00:29:11,083 --> 00:29:13,418
-Does he win a lot?
-Always.

487
00:29:13,627 --> 00:29:17,338
Why can't everyone just leave me alone?
Some sweaty fat guy blows his head off--

488
00:29:17,548 --> 00:29:19,799
-Why did you lie to the police?
-I didn't.

489
00:29:20,008 --> 00:29:23,386
Well, it says here in this paper
that you found Jerome Clifford dead.

490
00:29:23,804 --> 00:29:25,430
-I did.
-Uh-huh.

491
00:29:27,474 --> 00:29:31,185
Dead men don't sweat, now do they?

492
00:29:38,652 --> 00:29:41,237
If you was my lawyer...

493
00:29:41,447 --> 00:29:44,532
...and I told you something,
could you ever repeat it?

494
00:29:44,741 --> 00:29:47,493
No. What is it you wanna tell me?

495
00:29:48,662 --> 00:29:52,707
Well, that Clifford guy came driving up
in his big black car...

496
00:29:52,916 --> 00:29:57,462
...and me and Ricky, we snuck up to watch,
and that Clifford guy got out...

497
00:29:57,671 --> 00:30:00,965
...and he put a gun in his mouth
and he blew the back of his head out.

498
00:30:01,175 --> 00:30:03,301
So you did see Jerome Clifford alive?

499
00:30:04,470 --> 00:30:07,013
-Yeah.
-Why'd you lie to the police?

500
00:30:07,222 --> 00:30:09,891
I don't know.
I mean, I was just scared, I guess.

501
00:30:10,100 --> 00:30:13,478
My little brother's in a coma
and my mom might lose her job.

502
00:30:13,854 --> 00:30:16,147
The FBI’s after me
but I don't know nothing.

503
00:30:16,356 --> 00:30:17,565
You would lie too.

504
00:30:17,774 --> 00:30:21,903
Well, you're right,
you do need a lawyer, Mark Sway.

505
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:26,908
There are a few male lawyers down the hall.
You want me to recommend one?

506
00:30:27,993 --> 00:30:31,037
-How many cases have you won?
-More than I lost.

507
00:30:31,622 --> 00:30:34,957
-How much do you cost?
-How much you got?

508
00:30:52,267 --> 00:30:54,602
Nine thirty-two. Our boy has arrived.

509
00:30:59,983 --> 00:31:01,984
[MEN CHATTERING]

510
00:31:07,991 --> 00:31:10,701
Thank God your mother,
my sister, is dead, Barry.

511
00:31:11,078 --> 00:31:14,163
Having a son this stupid
would have killed her for sure.

512
00:31:15,582 --> 00:31:19,085
I told you not to hit Boyette, you did.

513
00:31:19,670 --> 00:31:23,172
I told you not to tell Romey too much,
you did.

514
00:31:23,382 --> 00:31:27,009
I hope it hurt that fat bastard.
I hope that bullet was slow.

515
00:31:27,219 --> 00:31:29,929
I hope he felt the top of his head
pull right off his face.

516
00:31:30,138 --> 00:31:33,975
Two kids found him, Barry,
maybe before he finished the job.

517
00:31:34,184 --> 00:31:37,728
-Yeah, I know, I seen it on TV.
-There's a chance he might have talked.

518
00:31:39,147 --> 00:31:41,649
Tell me Boyette's body's somewhere
the cops can't find.

519
00:31:41,858 --> 00:31:44,193
The cops are not gonna find the body.

520
00:31:44,403 --> 00:31:45,653
Move the body, Barry.

521
00:31:45,862 --> 00:31:48,281
I will, Uncle Johnny.

522
00:31:49,199 --> 00:31:51,242
Only I can't right now.

523
00:31:51,451 --> 00:31:52,952
Why?

524
00:31:54,955 --> 00:31:59,375
Where it's at, the body,
the cops are swarming all over the place.

525
00:32:00,002 --> 00:32:02,211
Don't worry,
they're not gonna find the body.

526
00:32:02,546 --> 00:32:06,841
If that kid knows anything, he's not talking,
otherwise I wouldn't be standing here.

527
00:32:07,050 --> 00:32:09,719
I'm going to Memphis
and I'm gonna take care of those kids.

528
00:32:09,886 --> 00:32:11,220
SULARI:
I'll tell you what you do.

529
00:32:11,430 --> 00:32:13,848
You just sit on your dumb ass.

530
00:32:14,850 --> 00:32:16,559
-Gronke.
-Mm-hm.

531
00:32:16,768 --> 00:32:19,812
SULARI: I want you in Memphis.
-Uh-huh.

532
00:32:22,566 --> 00:32:23,608
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

533
00:32:23,775 --> 00:32:25,276
MAN:
Come.

534
00:32:27,946 --> 00:32:29,697
Oh, you must be Mark.

535
00:32:29,906 --> 00:32:30,990
Hi, Mark.

536
00:32:31,199 --> 00:32:33,659
Jason McThune, Memphis FBI.

537
00:32:33,869 --> 00:32:36,412
This is Larry Trumann
from New Orleans FBI.

538
00:32:36,913 --> 00:32:39,749
This is Thomas Fink,
assistant United States attorney.. .

539
00:32:39,958 --> 00:32:42,043
...and Mr. Foltrigg, United States attorney.

540
00:32:42,711 --> 00:32:44,503
Both from southern Louisiana.

541
00:32:44,921 --> 00:32:45,963
Sit down, son.

542
00:32:47,799 --> 00:32:51,177
-Come on over here, Mark. Sit down.
-There you are.

543
00:32:53,347 --> 00:32:55,139
We expected your mother. Where is she?

544
00:32:55,807 --> 00:33:00,853
She's upstairs with my little brother.
She can't leave in case he wakes up.

545
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:05,483
But, you know,
we could hold this off for a couple of days.

546
00:33:05,692 --> 00:33:08,944
No, Mark,
let's talk a few minutes, just us.

547
00:33:12,574 --> 00:33:14,867
-You nervous?
-A little.

548
00:33:15,035 --> 00:33:16,661
[CHUCKLES]

549
00:33:16,828 --> 00:33:19,538
-Do I need a lawyer?
-Heh, what for?

550
00:33:19,748 --> 00:33:20,790
To protect my rights.

551
00:33:20,957 --> 00:33:22,708
FINK:
No, heh, you been watching too much TV.

552
00:33:22,876 --> 00:33:25,419
We just wanna ask you some questions.
You can trust us.

553
00:33:25,629 --> 00:33:28,756
Lawyers just get in the way.
They object to everything.

554
00:33:28,965 --> 00:33:31,008
What if I don't answer your questions?

555
00:33:31,218 --> 00:33:34,387
We might have to take you downtown.
Might take your mother too.

556
00:33:34,596 --> 00:33:36,514
-Will my mother get in trouble?
-Maybe.

557
00:33:36,723 --> 00:33:41,686
You ever hear of obstruction of justice,
Mark? It's a federal offense.

558
00:33:41,895 --> 00:33:44,188
It means if a man knows something
about a crime...

559
00:33:44,398 --> 00:33:48,275
...and withholds information from the FBI
or the police, well, he might be punished.

560
00:33:48,485 --> 00:33:50,653
You know,
sent to jail or something like that.

561
00:33:50,987 --> 00:33:55,449
So what you're trying to say is, is if I don't
answer your questions, I could go to jail?

562
00:33:55,659 --> 00:33:56,701
Maybe.

563
00:33:58,912 --> 00:34:02,456
Gosh, man, if y'all was in my place,
wouldn't y'all want a lawyer?

564
00:34:02,666 --> 00:34:05,584
Hell no, they're a pain in the ass.
You don't need a lawyer.

565
00:34:05,794 --> 00:34:07,962
-Pain in the ass?
-Mm-hm.

566
00:34:08,171 --> 00:34:09,672
But aren't you a lawyer?

567
00:34:10,424 --> 00:34:13,467
Jerome Clifford wasn't really dead
when you found him, was he?

568
00:34:13,677 --> 00:34:17,805
-Yes, he was.
-We know you were in that car, Mark.

569
00:34:18,598 --> 00:34:20,474
You see that?

570
00:34:21,685 --> 00:34:23,978
You and Romey had a nice long chat,
didn't you?

571
00:34:24,187 --> 00:34:28,149
What'd y'all talk about?
Did you talk about life? Talk about love?

572
00:34:29,192 --> 00:34:31,235
Y'all talk about where bodies are buried?

573
00:34:31,945 --> 00:34:33,404
I have to go to the bathroom.

574
00:34:33,613 --> 00:34:35,573
Answer the question first, please, Mark.

575
00:34:35,782 --> 00:34:37,491
I've gotta go bad. Please?

576
00:34:37,701 --> 00:34:38,909
Well, you'd better go.

577
00:34:39,119 --> 00:34:40,745
Thanks.

578
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:41,996
[DOOR OPENS]

579
00:34:42,164 --> 00:34:44,915
-Ha, ha.
-You don't need no stinking lawyer, heh.

580
00:34:45,083 --> 00:34:49,170
Hell no, heh. This boy's about ready
to tell all. You know where Muldano's at?

581
00:34:49,379 --> 00:34:53,257
-We're on his ass 24 hours a day.
-Better grab him so he don't skip town.

582
00:34:53,467 --> 00:34:56,218
Don't mark up his face.
We can do the press conference here.

583
00:34:56,428 --> 00:34:57,762
Hold on till we grab Muldano.

584
00:34:57,971 --> 00:35:01,056
I wanna make sure those affidavits are set
so he can't make bail.

585
00:35:01,224 --> 00:35:04,393
Did you get my makeup off the plane?
I'm gonna need Pancake number 17.

586
00:35:04,603 --> 00:35:06,645
Doughnuts. Doughnuts.
Give me that telephone.

587
00:35:06,855 --> 00:35:09,356
Press loves coffee and doughnuts.
See what you can do.

588
00:35:09,524 --> 00:35:11,150
Where we gonna put me?
Down by the flags?

589
00:35:11,318 --> 00:35:13,360
I think I look best
in front of these glass bricks. ..

590
00:35:13,528 --> 00:35:16,530
...behind a big bank of microphones.
That always looks nice, doesn't it, heh?

591
00:35:16,698 --> 00:35:17,740
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

592
00:35:17,908 --> 00:35:20,075
FINK: I'll call you back.
-Come in, Mark.

593
00:35:20,285 --> 00:35:22,369
-Polite kid.
-Yeah, he's a good boy.

594
00:35:25,832 --> 00:35:28,125
-Oh, keep your seats.
LARRY: We're in a meeting.

595
00:35:28,335 --> 00:35:30,920
McTHUNE: I think you're in the wrong room.
-I don't think so.

596
00:35:31,087 --> 00:35:35,591
Uh, my name is Reggie Love,
I'm an attorney and I represent Mark Sway.

597
00:35:36,551 --> 00:35:39,345
Uh, may I see some ID, please?

598
00:35:39,846 --> 00:35:41,639
When, uh, did he hire you?

599
00:35:41,848 --> 00:35:44,683
I don't think that's really
any of your business, now is it?

600
00:35:44,893 --> 00:35:46,519
Gonna have to forgive us, Ms. Love.

601
00:35:46,728 --> 00:35:49,772
You're so pretty, how could anybody
mistake you for a lawyer?

602
00:35:49,940 --> 00:35:51,106
[CHUCKLES]

603
00:35:51,274 --> 00:35:53,275
-Please, call me Reggie...
ROY: Reggie.

604
00:35:53,485 --> 00:35:54,527
...Roy.

605
00:35:55,028 --> 00:35:58,656
Uh-- So, uh, did you in fact--
Oh, please, sit down.

606
00:35:59,115 --> 00:36:04,662
--attempt to interrogate my client, uh,
outside the presence of his mother, Jason?

607
00:36:04,871 --> 00:36:06,163
No.

608
00:36:06,373 --> 00:36:08,999
He tells me that you did, Lawrence.

609
00:36:09,209 --> 00:36:11,001
He's confused.

610
00:36:11,211 --> 00:36:13,212
We assumed his mother
was on her way down.

611
00:36:13,421 --> 00:36:16,674
-Where were you during this?
-Oh, that's not really relevant.

612
00:36:16,883 --> 00:36:20,845
Uh, did you advise him
that he should talk to an attorney, Thomas?

613
00:36:21,054 --> 00:36:22,096
-No, uh-- Yes.
-Did I--?

614
00:36:22,305 --> 00:36:25,933
Remember, once, Larry, uh,
Mark said something, or I did, about TV...

615
00:36:26,142 --> 00:36:30,813
...and then, uh, Mark said that, heh,
he might need a lawyer...

616
00:36:31,022 --> 00:36:33,858
...and, uh, we--
I thought he was just joking.

617
00:36:34,651 --> 00:36:36,986
So he never asked you guys
if he needed a lawyer?

618
00:36:37,195 --> 00:36:39,196
I don't remember it that way.

619
00:36:39,489 --> 00:36:41,699
Did you advise him
of his Miranda rights?

620
00:36:41,908 --> 00:36:45,911
No, heh, what for? He's not a criminal.
We just wanted to ask him a few questions.

621
00:36:46,121 --> 00:36:49,415
You did attempt to interrogate him
outside the presence of his mother?

622
00:36:49,624 --> 00:36:51,125
McTHUNE: No.
-Definitely not.

623
00:36:51,334 --> 00:36:52,877
No way.

624
00:36:53,044 --> 00:36:54,461
[CHUCKLES]

625
00:36:55,922 --> 00:36:57,172
Bullshit.

626
00:36:57,340 --> 00:36:58,591
Uh.. ..

627
00:36:58,758 --> 00:37:02,052
Tread carefully. We know your client
lied about being in that car.

628
00:37:02,262 --> 00:37:05,723
I think that's a bit of the pot
calling the kettle black.

629
00:37:08,602 --> 00:37:10,853
MARK: Do I need a lawyer?
FINK: Heh, what for?

630
00:37:11,021 --> 00:37:12,062
MARK:
To protect my rights.

631
00:37:12,230 --> 00:37:13,981
FINK:
No, heh, you been watching too much TV.

632
00:37:14,149 --> 00:37:16,483
LARRY: We just wanna ask some questions.
You can trust us.

633
00:37:16,693 --> 00:37:21,071
FINK: Lawyers just get in the way.
They object to everything.

634
00:37:21,281 --> 00:37:24,658
-You wired the kid.
-It's nothing personal, Lawrence.

635
00:37:24,868 --> 00:37:26,201
McTHUNE:
--take your mother too.

636
00:37:26,620 --> 00:37:28,454
You attempted to interrogate a child. ..

637
00:37:28,663 --> 00:37:31,498
...outside the presence of his mother
and without her consent.

638
00:37:31,708 --> 00:37:34,501
He asked you if he needed a lawyer
and you said no...

639
00:37:34,711 --> 00:37:37,880
...stating as one of your reasons
that lawyers are a pain in the ass.

640
00:37:38,089 --> 00:37:39,840
I'd like to confer with my client.. .

641
00:37:40,050 --> 00:37:42,927
...and meet with you people in my office
tomorrow around 3:00.

642
00:37:43,637 --> 00:37:49,183
And if I need anything from you boys,
like the truth, well I expect to get it.

643
00:37:49,392 --> 00:37:51,477
I catch you lying again...

644
00:37:51,686 --> 00:37:53,228
... I'm gonna use the tape.

645
00:37:55,231 --> 00:37:57,232
That's blackmail, Ms. Love.

646
00:37:57,442 --> 00:37:58,859
Indict me, Reverend Roy.

647
00:37:59,277 --> 00:38:00,861
[DOOR OPENS]

648
00:38:01,321 --> 00:38:02,363
[CHUCKLES]

649
00:38:02,530 --> 00:38:03,572
[DOOR CLOSES]

650
00:38:03,740 --> 00:38:05,115
McTHUNE:
Still want those doughnuts?

651
00:38:05,283 --> 00:38:08,827
Shut up, McThune. Goddamn.

652
00:38:09,037 --> 00:38:11,830
DIANNE: You want a cigarette?
REGGIE: Oh, no thanks, I just quit.

653
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:14,792
DIANNE: There's been a mistake, ma'am.
We can't afford no lawyer.

654
00:38:15,001 --> 00:38:18,212
REGGIE: Don't worry about the money.
DIANE: My pig boss fired me this morning.

655
00:38:18,421 --> 00:38:21,590
I mean, my baby's in a coma
and he fires me.

656
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:25,469
-Don't tell Mark.
-Just one day and he fired you? He is a pig.

657
00:38:25,679 --> 00:38:26,720
Sucks.

658
00:38:26,930 --> 00:38:30,349
Wasn't much of a job anyways.
Five bucks an hour at a lamp factory.

659
00:38:30,517 --> 00:38:32,810
How long you been working there?

660
00:38:32,978 --> 00:38:34,019
Huh?

661
00:38:34,187 --> 00:38:35,938
-How long you been--?
-Oh, uh. ... Six months.

662
00:38:36,106 --> 00:38:37,147
Oh.

663
00:38:37,315 --> 00:38:40,901
-Lord, I can't keep my head on straight.
-You're doing fine.

664
00:38:41,695 --> 00:38:43,737
I like your ring.

665
00:38:43,947 --> 00:38:45,406
They real diamonds?

666
00:38:45,615 --> 00:38:49,159
Lord, no. It's semi-precious.

667
00:38:50,203 --> 00:38:52,371
You got kids?

668
00:38:54,040 --> 00:38:58,460
Gosh, you must have been just a baby
when you started having your babies.

669
00:38:59,045 --> 00:39:03,340
I was just a dumb kid living in a dream.

670
00:39:03,633 --> 00:39:07,886
All I ever wanted was a white house
with a walk-in closet.

671
00:39:08,054 --> 00:39:09,096
[CHUCKLES]

672
00:39:09,264 --> 00:39:11,223
Ain't that stupid?

673
00:39:11,725 --> 00:39:15,561
No. Having a dream's never stupid.

674
00:39:17,063 --> 00:39:20,107
Take it one day at a time,
that's what I say.

675
00:39:21,901 --> 00:39:25,154
[MIMICKING GUITAR]

676
00:39:28,491 --> 00:39:31,118
Come on, Ricky,
you always laugh at my air guitar.

677
00:39:31,494 --> 00:39:33,871
Who's the best guitarist
in the whole world? Who?

678
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:36,165
Come on, Ricky, say it.

679
00:39:36,374 --> 00:39:38,042
Yell it.

680
00:39:38,793 --> 00:39:40,878
I know, heh.

681
00:39:41,046 --> 00:39:43,464
Ah, look, Ricky, an Eskimo pissing.

682
00:39:43,631 --> 00:39:46,050
[GROANING]

683
00:39:47,010 --> 00:39:48,635
[SIGHS]

684
00:39:52,932 --> 00:39:56,101
Ricky, look at you.

685
00:39:56,603 --> 00:39:57,770
[SIGHS]

686
00:39:57,937 --> 00:40:01,690
I shouldn't have made you stay
in those woods. It's my fault.

687
00:40:02,275 --> 00:40:05,069
But things are gonna be all right,
Ricky, I swear.

688
00:40:05,278 --> 00:40:06,862
I've got us a lawyer...

689
00:40:07,072 --> 00:40:10,908
...and even though she is a woman,
she's pretty darn good, heh.

690
00:40:11,117 --> 00:40:14,036
She only costs a dollar too, heh.

691
00:40:14,621 --> 00:40:16,955
That's not it though.

692
00:40:18,541 --> 00:40:20,375
I'm really sorry.

693
00:40:21,044 --> 00:40:22,461
I'm gonna make it up to you.

694
00:40:23,004 --> 00:40:24,046
I promise.

695
00:40:24,214 --> 00:40:25,255
[CAMERA CLICKING]

696
00:40:25,423 --> 00:40:26,882
Hey.

697
00:40:27,092 --> 00:40:30,552
-What the hell are you doing?
-Hi, Slick Moeller, Memphis Press.

698
00:40:30,762 --> 00:40:33,138
I wrote the story this morning.
How's your brother?

699
00:40:33,348 --> 00:40:35,516
-Get out of here! Get out!
-How's your brother?

700
00:40:35,725 --> 00:40:38,352
Heh, just a second, son,
I just wanna ask you a few questions.

701
00:40:38,561 --> 00:40:42,231
-Did Clifford touch you any place?
-Get out! Just shut up!

702
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:45,192
Did he tell you why
he was committing suicide?

703
00:40:45,401 --> 00:40:47,069
-Did he?
-You better get out of here.

704
00:40:47,278 --> 00:40:49,113
-Did he talk to you at all?
-Get out!

705
00:40:49,322 --> 00:40:51,824
I'll tell you what, I'll pay you.
