How's your brother doing?

939
00:56:33,265 --> 00:56:34,557
Come on back here.

940
00:56:34,767 --> 00:56:38,770
-Elvis has left the building.
-Told you so.

941
00:56:38,937 --> 00:56:40,354
[DOOR CLOSES]

942
00:56:42,649 --> 00:56:45,610
MOMMA: Why, hello there.
-Take me back to the hospital.

943
00:56:46,028 --> 00:56:48,404
-Want some lemonade?
-I'm not taking you anywhere...

944
00:56:48,614 --> 00:56:51,115
-...until we've had a conversation.
-Or a piece of pie?

945
00:56:51,325 --> 00:56:53,493
Where's a phone? I need to call a cab.

946
00:56:53,702 --> 00:56:56,287
Help yourself.
It's, uh, 40 dollars from here, Momma?

947
00:56:56,455 --> 00:56:59,248
Or 45? I'm not sure, something with a tip.

948
00:56:59,792 --> 00:57:03,002
Look, you're fired, okay?
Can't you get that through your thick head?

949
00:57:03,212 --> 00:57:06,839
Fine. Because I cannot do my job
if you keep hiding things from me.

950
00:57:07,049 --> 00:57:11,427
Did it ever occur to you how it made me
feel to take on Foltrigg on your behalf.. .

951
00:57:11,637 --> 00:57:13,012
...without the facts?

952
00:57:13,222 --> 00:57:15,640
I should've smelled your breath
before I hired you. ..

953
00:57:15,849 --> 00:57:19,560
-...then I would've known you was a drunk.
-Well, I think I'll be going.

954
00:57:19,770 --> 00:57:22,021
I have been sober for 3 years.

955
00:57:22,231 --> 00:57:26,192
Yeah, right. That's what all the drunks say.
How they gonna get sober and all.

956
00:57:26,401 --> 00:57:28,653
They even say they love you,
but they don't.

957
00:57:28,862 --> 00:57:32,031
Then they come home wasted
and beat on you and your mother so bad...

958
00:57:32,241 --> 00:57:34,742
...you gotta hit them in the face
with a baseball bat.

959
00:57:35,410 --> 00:57:37,453
You're talking about your daddy,
aren't you?

960
00:57:37,663 --> 00:57:39,914
Yeah, well I got rid of him.

961
00:57:40,249 --> 00:57:42,750
When me and my mom went into court
to buy a divorce...

962
00:57:42,960 --> 00:57:44,585
...our lawyer sucked, as usual.

963
00:57:44,795 --> 00:57:48,840
So I went up there and told the judge
myself about all the beatings...

964
00:57:49,508 --> 00:57:52,176
...and about how
he made us sleep in the street.

965
00:57:52,803 --> 00:57:55,429
And that's when my father
became my ex-father.

966
00:57:55,639 --> 00:57:59,559
And now I got you,
and you're a drunk and a bad lawyer too.

967
00:57:59,768 --> 00:58:02,103
So now I'm getting rid of you.
You're fired, okay?

968
00:58:02,312 --> 00:58:05,022
I can handle this myself.

969
00:58:07,276 --> 00:58:08,693
Mark.

970
00:58:08,902 --> 00:58:12,321
Mark, I used to think
I could handle everything by myself.

971
00:58:12,531 --> 00:58:15,575
But sometimes being strong
means asking for help.

972
00:58:15,784 --> 00:58:18,536
I know you've been taking
real good care of your family.. .

973
00:58:18,745 --> 00:58:21,205
...but the FBI’s
not gonna leave you alone.

974
00:58:22,749 --> 00:58:25,668
-You gotta let me help you.
-Let go.

975
00:58:25,878 --> 00:58:29,005
-I need a cigarette.
-Smoking is terrible for you.

976
00:58:29,214 --> 00:58:31,465
Hey, hey, hey.

977
00:58:31,758 --> 00:58:33,467
What did Romey tell you in that car?

978
00:58:33,677 --> 00:58:35,845
God, why do I always
have to answer questions?

979
00:58:36,054 --> 00:58:38,848
Why don't you ever have to
answer any questions?

980
00:58:39,057 --> 00:58:41,434
Okay, that's fair.
Go ahead, ask me something.

981
00:58:41,643 --> 00:58:42,768
Like what?

982
00:58:43,478 --> 00:58:46,856
Whatever you want. Go ahead,
there's no rules, there's no limits.

983
00:58:47,065 --> 00:58:49,317
You ask me and I will answer.

984
00:58:49,526 --> 00:58:50,776
And you'll tell the truth?

985
00:58:50,986 --> 00:58:53,404
If it takes my skin off.

986
00:58:54,406 --> 00:58:55,448
All right.

987
00:58:56,200 --> 00:58:58,993
What's that thing you always wear
around your neck?

988
00:58:59,203 --> 00:59:01,954
This is my mamaw's compass.

989
00:59:02,456 --> 00:59:04,749
I wear it so I'll never lose my way again.

990
00:59:04,917 --> 00:59:06,375
Hmm.

991
00:59:07,419 --> 00:59:08,920
Anything else?

992
00:59:09,129 --> 00:59:11,380
Yeah. These your kids?

993
00:59:11,590 --> 00:59:14,508
-Yes.
-They chained down in the basement?

994
00:59:14,676 --> 00:59:16,510
Heh, close. They're with their daddy.

995
00:59:16,720 --> 00:59:18,721
-There was a divorce.
-You ever see them?

996
00:59:20,265 --> 00:59:23,851
-They don't really wanna see me.
-Because you was drunk and on drugs.

997
00:59:24,686 --> 00:59:27,563
Because after the divorce
I drank some, yes.

998
00:59:31,443 --> 00:59:32,568
I drank a lot.

999
00:59:34,988 --> 00:59:36,614
Why?

1000
00:59:39,034 --> 00:59:42,286
You're right, there must be a cigarette
around here someplace.

1001
00:59:43,497 --> 00:59:47,583
Uh, I married a big Memphis doctor, worked my
ass off to put him through medical school. ..

1002
00:59:47,793 --> 00:59:51,921
...and soon as he became rich and famous,
he traded me in for a younger model.

1003
00:59:58,971 --> 01:00:01,389
I didn't have a dollar
to put food in the fridge. ..

1004
01:00:01,598 --> 01:00:04,267
...or a car to go look for a job.

1005
01:00:04,476 --> 01:00:08,062
But I figured I could handle it myself,
just like you.

1006
01:00:09,815 --> 01:00:11,649
But I was wrong.

1007
01:00:11,858 --> 01:00:14,277
-So then you started to drink?
-Mm-mm.

1008
01:00:15,320 --> 01:00:18,823
First, I stopped sleeping and eating.

1009
01:00:19,241 --> 01:00:22,702
I was scared to death. I kept staying up
every night, watching my babies. ..

1010
01:00:22,911 --> 01:00:24,996
...trying to figure out
what I was gonna do.

1011
01:00:25,205 --> 01:00:27,832
Finally, I took some pills to sleep.

1012
01:00:28,250 --> 01:00:32,712
Hell, he prescribed them for me.
I was not trying to kill myself.

1013
01:00:34,006 --> 01:00:36,424
But that's when he pounced.

1014
01:00:36,675 --> 01:00:38,968
Got himself a fancy lawyer.

1015
01:00:39,177 --> 01:00:40,803
I didn't have anybody.

1016
01:00:41,013 --> 01:00:44,724
I figured after all those years
of blowing noses and wiping butts...

1017
01:00:44,933 --> 01:00:47,184
...fixing meals and carpooling
the kids every which way...

1018
01:00:47,352 --> 01:00:49,603
...that it'd count for something.

1019
01:00:50,188 --> 01:00:52,398
I was a fool.

1020
01:00:54,192 --> 01:00:56,277
The court declared me unfit.

1021
01:00:57,779 --> 01:01:01,324
Just like that, they were gone.

1022
01:01:02,200 --> 01:01:03,743
He took...

1023
01:01:04,202 --> 01:01:06,537
...my little girl and my little boy, heh.

1024
01:01:06,747 --> 01:01:09,874
Anyhow, that's when I started drinking.

1025
01:01:10,208 --> 01:01:12,668
But I got myself sober.. .

1026
01:01:13,045 --> 01:01:14,128
... I stayed sober. ..

1027
01:01:15,130 --> 01:01:17,173
...and I put myself through law school.

1028
01:01:19,468 --> 01:01:22,219
-Do you miss your kids?
-Heh.

1029
01:01:24,473 --> 01:01:27,516
So much
I try not to even think about them.

1030
01:01:53,001 --> 01:01:55,252
He told me.

1031
01:01:56,213 --> 01:01:58,172
Romey told me where the body's buried.

1032
01:01:59,841 --> 01:02:01,842
Do you wanna tell me?

1033
01:02:02,052 --> 01:02:04,553
I can call the police
and put an end to this right now.

1034
01:02:04,763 --> 01:02:07,473
But I swore an oath
that I wouldn't tell nobody.

1035
01:02:08,392 --> 01:02:11,644
They're gonna get me, Reggie.
I seen it on TV.

1036
01:02:11,853 --> 01:02:13,771
The Mob never forgets.

1037
01:02:14,231 --> 01:02:16,315
Oh, my God.
They came after you, didn't they?

1038
01:02:17,692 --> 01:02:20,361
-Yes, ma'am.
-I gotta get security on your brother's room.

1039
01:02:20,570 --> 01:02:22,738
And notify the police
and get you out of here...

1040
01:02:22,948 --> 01:02:25,324
...back to the hospital
where you'll be safe.

1041
01:02:25,700 --> 01:02:27,410
Reggie. ..

1042
01:02:27,619 --> 01:02:29,537
... I'm scared.

1043
01:02:46,721 --> 01:02:48,514
What's up?

1044
01:02:50,100 --> 01:02:53,894
He's in there. But y'all gonna have
to deal with the two bitches.

1045
01:02:54,396 --> 01:02:56,313
What do you think?

1046
01:02:58,608 --> 01:03:00,109
I got an idea.

1047
01:03:00,277 --> 01:03:01,652
[CHATTERING]

1048
01:03:01,820 --> 01:03:05,156
It's gonna take at least a week
to get that kid into protective custody.

1049
01:03:05,365 --> 01:03:07,324
We still gotta find a way
to make him talk.

1050
01:03:07,534 --> 01:03:10,077
I want that kid in court
and on the stand mañana.

1051
01:03:10,287 --> 01:03:12,329
-You hear what I'm telling you?
-Yes, but--

1052
01:03:12,539 --> 01:03:14,707
Let me have the phone.
I know how to solve this.

1053
01:03:14,916 --> 01:03:18,544
Don't you have something to do?
Why don't you go wake somebody up?

1054
01:03:19,963 --> 01:03:22,798
-Mr. Foltrigg? May I have your autograph?
-Of course you can.

1055
01:03:23,008 --> 01:03:26,177
Thomas, let me encourage you
to produce me some immediate results.. .

1056
01:03:26,386 --> 01:03:30,681
...in the interest of your own personal
job security right, by God, now.

1057
01:03:30,891 --> 01:03:31,932
What's your name?

1058
01:04:06,009 --> 01:04:07,801
Our trailer....

1059
01:04:08,512 --> 01:04:12,389
They burned down our home.
We got nothing left.

1060
01:04:13,058 --> 01:04:14,099
Who did?

1061
01:04:14,309 --> 01:04:15,726
How the hell do I know?

1062
01:04:15,936 --> 01:04:20,314
Somebody, they saw two people,
they was leaving and.. ..

1063
01:04:20,524 --> 01:04:22,775
It's all gone. All of it.

1064
01:04:23,610 --> 01:04:25,569
-Mom, it's my fault.
-Dianne, I'm so sorry.

1065
01:04:26,363 --> 01:04:29,657
Look, it's gonna be all right.
Do you know if you have insurance?

1066
01:04:29,866 --> 01:04:32,368
That is none of your business, really.

1067
01:04:32,577 --> 01:04:34,620
REGGIE:
I'm sorry, I didn't mean anything by it.

1068
01:04:35,247 --> 01:04:37,998
-I was just trying to help, is all.
-What is this crap?

1069
01:04:38,166 --> 01:04:39,208
Oh, heh.

1070
01:04:39,376 --> 01:04:42,169
A few things I put together
to make you feel more comfortable--

1071
01:04:42,379 --> 01:04:45,256
-I don't need your charity.
-It's not charity--

1072
01:04:45,465 --> 01:04:48,592
DIANNE: And I don't need you trying
to come in here and take away my son.

1073
01:04:48,802 --> 01:04:53,222
-Mark's already got a mother!
REGGIE: I know that. You're doing a fine job.

1074
01:04:53,431 --> 01:04:55,516
DIANNE: I don't need your help.
-Look, I'm sorry--

1075
01:04:55,725 --> 01:04:56,892
Get out!

1076
01:05:02,357 --> 01:05:04,191
Sure.

1077
01:05:08,321 --> 01:05:09,363
Reggie.

1078
01:05:09,573 --> 01:05:12,074
-Reggie, you okay?
-I'm fine.

1079
01:05:12,534 --> 01:05:14,660
HOOSER:
They got her on all kinds of medication.

1080
01:05:14,828 --> 01:05:17,037
She doesn't know what she's saying.

1081
01:05:18,540 --> 01:05:22,209
I had no call
to speak to her that way, Lord.

1082
01:05:22,836 --> 01:05:24,503
-I'm sorry.
-It's all right.

1083
01:05:24,671 --> 01:05:25,879
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

1084
01:05:27,382 --> 01:05:28,841
Hello.

1085
01:05:29,217 --> 01:05:31,093
I'm Detective Ed Nassar, Memphis P.D.

1086
01:05:31,303 --> 01:05:32,886
-You Dianne Sway?
-Yeah.

1087
01:05:33,096 --> 01:05:36,557
These are from juvenile court. It's a
summons for a hearing at 10 tomorrow.

1088
01:05:36,766 --> 01:05:40,019
The summons requires us to take
young Mark into custody at this time.

1089
01:05:40,228 --> 01:05:42,396
What? You can't take my son.

1090
01:05:42,606 --> 01:05:44,773
-Well, we're gonna have to.
-You son of a bitch.

1091
01:05:44,983 --> 01:05:46,775
-Easy now.
-Over my dead body.

1092
01:05:46,985 --> 01:05:50,529
-It's for his own good.
-What's he done? Just tell me.

1093
01:05:50,697 --> 01:05:52,156
Can somebody help me?
Don't touch him.

1094
01:05:52,324 --> 01:05:54,742
NASSAR: The petition was filed
because he will not cooperate--

1095
01:05:54,909 --> 01:05:55,951
Son of a bitch!

1096
01:05:56,119 --> 01:05:57,411
-Come on. Come on.
DIANNE: Help.

1097
01:05:57,579 --> 01:05:58,996
[NASSAR GRUNTS]

1098
01:05:59,164 --> 01:06:02,625
NASSAR: Come on. Calm down. Calm down.
DIANNE: Unh, help me.

1099
01:06:02,792 --> 01:06:03,834
[ALL GRUNT]

1100
01:06:04,002 --> 01:06:05,252
-Mark.
HARDY: Come on.

1101
01:06:05,420 --> 01:06:08,172
NASSAR: There's no reason to get excited.
We'll take good care of him.

1102
01:06:08,340 --> 01:06:09,381
[DIANNE GRUNTS]

1103
01:06:09,549 --> 01:06:11,258
NASSAR: Give it up. Come on.
-Get off of me!

1104
01:06:11,468 --> 01:06:14,219
Come on, now,
you're getting yourself all riled up.

1105
01:06:14,387 --> 01:06:16,347
Agh!

1106
01:06:16,514 --> 01:06:18,349
[SCREAMS]

1107
01:06:18,516 --> 01:06:21,060
They're taking me to jail!
I'm an 11-year-old!

1108
01:06:21,269 --> 01:06:23,145
-They hit my mother!
-Shut up, Markus.

1109
01:06:23,355 --> 01:06:25,314
Hey, you gonna read me my rights?

1110
01:06:25,523 --> 01:06:28,025
Hey, meathead,
you even know how to read?

1111
01:06:28,234 --> 01:06:30,235
-You gonna cuff me?
-This is not an arrest.

1112
01:06:30,445 --> 01:06:32,821
-Then what the hell is it?
-Watch your mouth, kid.

1113
01:06:33,031 --> 01:06:35,449
Kiss my ass, you stupid jerk.

1114
01:06:35,617 --> 01:06:37,242
[ALL SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

1115
01:06:44,876 --> 01:06:46,168
He's all yours.

1116
01:06:46,336 --> 01:06:47,878
Oh.

1117
01:06:48,046 --> 01:06:49,755
Calm down.

1118
01:06:50,757 --> 01:06:53,050
Empty your pockets.

1119
01:06:55,011 --> 01:06:56,553
[INMATES SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

1120
01:07:00,016 --> 01:07:03,018
WOMAN:
Okay, now follow me.

1121
01:07:03,186 --> 01:07:04,812
McTHUNE: There you are.
-I don't look bad.

1122
01:07:04,979 --> 01:07:06,021
McTHUNE:
You look good.

1123
01:07:06,189 --> 01:07:07,231
[PHONE RINGS]

1124
01:07:07,399 --> 01:07:09,358
-Ahem, all right.
LARRY: Unh.

1125
01:07:09,567 --> 01:07:12,236
-Hello?
-I twisted every arm, I broke every leg.

1126
01:07:12,445 --> 01:07:14,446
You got what you want.
The kid's in custody.

1127
01:07:14,656 --> 01:07:18,033
-You got your hearing tomorrow at 10a.m.
-I knew you could do it, Jason.

1128
01:07:18,243 --> 01:07:19,952
Well done, heh.

1129
01:07:20,161 --> 01:07:22,162
-One child in jail.
-All right.

1130
01:07:22,330 --> 01:07:24,248
[WOMEN SCREAMING]

1131
01:07:28,795 --> 01:07:31,964
-What kind of place is this?
-Women's detention hall.

1132
01:07:34,801 --> 01:07:37,928
-Keep the noise down!
-Why am I being put in with the women?

1133
01:07:38,138 --> 01:07:39,555
Because you're a minor.

1134
01:07:39,764 --> 01:07:42,433
Stop treating me like a kid.
Put me where the men are.

1135
01:07:42,642 --> 01:07:47,062
You're safer here.
You have this whole cell to yourself.

1136
01:07:47,272 --> 01:07:50,232
-Is this what they mean by solitary?
-No.

1137
01:07:50,442 --> 01:07:53,652
You can have any bed you want.
Don't give me any trouble.

1138
01:08:00,660 --> 01:08:02,536
You okay, boy?

1139
01:08:03,163 --> 01:08:04,955
Can I call my mom?

1140
01:08:05,165 --> 01:08:08,500
Just to tell her where I'm at
and that I'm okay.

1141
01:08:08,710 --> 01:08:12,171
Please, she's probably
worried sick about me.

1142
01:08:13,840 --> 01:08:16,550
I suppose I could run a phone in here.

1143
01:08:16,760 --> 01:08:19,428
I'll make this little exception,
just this once.

1144
01:08:19,637 --> 01:08:21,472
Thank you, ma'am.

1145
01:08:23,975 --> 01:08:26,101
[LINE RINGS]

1146
01:08:26,269 --> 01:08:28,228
WOMAN [OVER PHONE]:
Brother's Pizza.

1147
01:08:28,438 --> 01:08:31,899
Uh, yes, I would like to order
20 of your largest Supremes.

1148
01:08:32,108 --> 01:08:34,276
Okay, and where's that going, honey?

1149
01:08:34,486 --> 01:08:37,446
Uh, I'm ordering for Detective Nassar,
North Precinct.

1150
01:08:37,655 --> 01:08:40,324
Okay, and how would you like to pay
for this order?

1151
01:08:40,533 --> 01:08:43,452
-Well, with my credit card.
-Number, please.

1152
01:08:43,661 --> 01:08:49,082
The number is 4000-0306.. .

1153
01:08:49,292 --> 01:08:52,961
...1954-0010.

1154
01:08:53,171 --> 01:08:55,464
Okay, hold on.

1155
01:08:55,757 --> 01:08:58,592
That'll be $248.10.

1156
01:08:58,802 --> 01:09:00,886
Fine. Cheaper than the last time.

1157
01:09:01,095 --> 01:09:03,722
-Oh, well.
-Thank you.

1158
01:09:04,849 --> 01:09:06,266
[CHUCKLES]

1159
01:09:09,020 --> 01:09:12,105
REGGIE: We'll never get him out tonight.
Foltrigg filed a custody petition.

1160
01:09:12,315 --> 01:09:14,316
-Roosevelt scheduled a hearing for 10.
-Ten?

1161
01:09:14,526 --> 01:09:17,569
There's three to seven days
after filing a petition, not hours.

1162
01:09:17,737 --> 01:09:19,530
REGGIE:
That damn Foltrigg, he'll do anything.

1163
01:09:19,697 --> 01:09:22,324
HOOSER: Got that right.
REGGIE: A child behind bars for the night.

1164
01:09:22,534 --> 01:09:27,162
I have been through this wallet three times,
I have found everything except my Visa.

1165
01:09:27,372 --> 01:09:28,664
MAN:
Man, these things are hot.

1166
01:09:28,832 --> 01:09:31,792
Hi. Did y'all order the pizzas?

1167
01:09:46,015 --> 01:09:47,641
[SIGHS]

1168
01:10:00,405 --> 01:10:02,614
[MUTTERING]

1169
01:10:03,658 --> 01:10:05,075
